						<summary>

						

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Vīrapratāpa Gajavēṭṭaikāṟa Dēvarāya (II) Year: Śaka 1358 <hi rend="italic">Naḷa, Tai Saṅkarmaṇa</hi> = 1436-37 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that the weavers <hi rend="italic">(kaikkoḷa)</hi> who were residing at the quarters around the Tiruvāṉiśvaram-uḍaiya nāyaṉār temple at Nerumūr in Kaḷattūr-paṟṟu were to remit two <hi rend="italic">paṇam</hi> as <hi rend="italic">paṭṭaḍai-nūlāyam</hi> per loom annually. Any violation to this arrangement would be deemed as the sin of killing tawny cow on the bank of the river Ganges.</p>						

						</summary>
